sourcesContent:
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useParams, Link } from 'react-router-dom';
import { 
  Box, Typography, Button, Grid, Card, CardContent, Breadcrumbs, 
  Tabs, Tab, List, ListItem, ListItemIcon, ListItemText, Divider, 
  Chip, Rating, Avatar, LinearProgress, Paper 
} from '@mui/material';
import { 
  PlayArrow, Assignment, MenuBook, Check, PlayCircleOutline, 
  BarChart, People, Schedule, AutoStories, ArrowBack, BookmarkAdd 
} from '@mui/icons-material';

const ModuleDetail = () => {
  const { id } = useParams();
  const [tabValue, setTabValue] = useState(0);
  const [module, setModule] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  // Fetch module data
  useEffect(() => {
    // Simulating API fetch
    setTimeout(() => {
      // This would normally be an API call
      const moduleData = {
        id: 23,
        title: 'RISC-V Processor Design',
        description: 'Design a complete RISC-V processor from scratch in Verilog. Implement the RV32I instruction set with pipelining, hazard resolution, and branch prediction. This comprehensive module will take you from basic architecture concepts to a fully functional processor implementation that can run real programs.',
        image: 'https://via.placeholder.com/1200x600?text=RISC-V+Processor+Design',
        level: 'Expert',
        category: 'Processor Design',
        rating: 4.9,
        studentsCount: 465,
        updatedAt: '2023-11-15T12:00:00Z',
        duration: '40-50 hours',
        prerequisites: [
          'Verilog Fundamentals',
          'Combinational Circuits',
          'Sequential Circuits',
          'Finite State Machines'
        ],
        objectives: [
          'Understand the RISC-V architecture and instruction set',
          'Design a single-cycle processor implementation in Verilog',
          'Upgrade to a pipelined architecture for improved performance',
          'Implement hazard detection and forwarding logic',
          'Add branch prediction for better performance',
          'Verify the processor design through simulation',
          'Implement the design on an FPGA platform',
          'Run benchmark programs on your processor'
        ],
        skills: [
          'RISC-V Architecture',
          'Processor Design',
          'Pipelining',
          'Hazard Resolution',
          'Branch Prediction',
          'RTL Implementation',
          'FPGA Prototyping',
          'Verification'
        ],
        instructor: {
          name: 'Dr. Michael Reynolds',
          avatar: 'https://via.placeholder.com/100?text=M.R.',
          bio: 'Dr. Reynolds has 15+ years of industry experience designing processors at Arm and Intel. He holds 12 patents in processor architecture and has contributed to multiple commercial CPU cores used in billions of devices worldwide.',
          experience: '15+ years in industry',
          company: 'Former Principal Architect at Arm',
          credentials: 'Ph.D. in Computer Architecture, Stanford University'
        },
        overview: `
The RISC-V Processor Design module provides a comprehensive journey through modern processor design using the open RISC-V instruction set architecture. This module is specifically designed for engineers and students who want to gain practical experience in implementing a complete processor from scratch.

Throughout this module, you'll implement a complete RV32I processor core in Verilog HDL. Starting with a basic single-cycle implementation, you'll gradually enhance your design to incorporate pipelining, hazard resolution mechanisms, and branch prediction techniques commonly found in modern processors.

Key industry-relevant aspects of this module include:

1. **Hands-on implementation:** Every architectural concept is immediately followed by practical Verilog implementation, ensuring you can translate theory into working hardware.

2. **Industry-standard practices:** The coding guidelines and verification methodologies taught in this module reflect current industry practices used at leading semiconductor companies.

3. **Performance optimization:** You'll learn how to analyze and improve the performance of your processor using techniques employed in commercial designs.

4. **FPGA implementation:** The module concludes with deploying your processor on an FPGA platform and running real benchmark programs, providing end-to-end design experience.

The skills gained from this module are directly applicable to roles in processor design teams, SoC development, FPGA prototyping, and hardware verification positions at semiconductor companies.
`,
        lessons: [
          {
            id: 1,
            title: 'Introduction to RISC-V Architecture',
            duration: '90 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Overview of the RISC-V ISA, its design philosophy, and basic instruction formats. Comparison with other popular architectures like ARM and x86.',
            topics: [
              'RISC-V History and Philosophy',
              'RISC vs CISC Trade-offs',
              'RV32I Base Integer Instruction Set',
              'Instruction Formats and Encoding',
              'RISC-V Extension Mechanisms',
              'Comparison with ARM and x86'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'RISC-V ISA Specification',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Lecture Slides',
                type: 'slides',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 2,
            title: 'Processor Building Blocks',
            duration: '120 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Design and implementation of the key components needed for our processor including the ALU, register file, and control unit.',
            topics: [
              'ALU Design for RISC-V',
              'Register File Implementation',
              'Immediate Generator',
              'Control Unit Design',
              'Memory Interface'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'ALU Implementation Slides',
                type: 'slides',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Register File Verilog Code',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 3,
            title: 'Single-Cycle Processor Implementation',
            duration: '180 min',
            type: 'hands-on',
            description: 'Implement a complete single-cycle RV32I processor capable of executing basic instructions. Integration of all building blocks into a functional design.',
            topics: [
              'Instruction Fetch Stage',
              'Instruction Decode Logic',
              'Execution Unit Integration',
              'Memory Access Stage',
              'Write-Back Logic',
              'Control Signal Generation',
              'Data Path Implementation'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Single-Cycle Datapath Diagram',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'CPU Module Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 4,
            title: 'Lab: Testing the Single-Cycle Processor',
            duration: '150 min',
            type: 'lab',
            description: 'Develop a testbench to verify the functionality of your single-cycle processor. Run simple RISC-V programs and debug implementation issues.',
            topics: [
              'Testbench Development',
              'Assembly Program Creation',
              'Instruction Memory Initialization',
              'Waveform Analysis',
              'Debugging Techniques',
              'Performance Measurement'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Testbench Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Sample RISC-V Programs',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 5,
            title: 'Introduction to Pipelining',
            duration: '120 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Principles of processor pipelining, performance benefits, challenges, and implementation considerations for a RISC-V pipeline.',
            topics: [
              'Pipeline Concepts and Benefits',
              'Five-Stage RISC Pipeline',
              'Pipeline Registers Design',
              'Pipeline Hazards Overview',
              'Performance Analysis'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Pipelining Concepts Slides',
                type: 'slides',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Pipeline Registers Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 6,
            title: 'Pipelined Processor Implementation',
            duration: '210 min',
            type: 'hands-on',
            description: 'Convert the single-cycle processor into a pipelined implementation. Design and integrate pipeline registers and modify the control logic.',
            topics: [
              'Pipeline Stage Division',
              'Pipeline Register Implementation',
              'Control Signal Propagation',
              'Structural Hazard Handling',
              'Pipeline Timing Analysis'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Pipelined Datapath Diagram',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Pipeline Register Verilog Code',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 7,
            title: 'Hazard Detection and Forwarding',
            duration: '180 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Comprehensive coverage of data hazards, forwarding paths, and stall logic required for correct pipelined execution.',
            topics: [
              'Data Hazard Types and Detection',
              'Forwarding Logic Design',
              'Forwarding Paths Implementation',
              'Stall Logic for Load Hazards',
              'Performance Impact Analysis'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Hazard Unit Diagram',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Forwarding Unit Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 8,
            title: 'Lab: Hazard Resolution Implementation',
            duration: '180 min',
            type: 'lab',
            description: 'Implement and test hazard detection and forwarding logic in your pipelined processor. Verify correct execution with hazard-prone code sequences.',
            topics: [
              'Forwarding Unit Implementation',
              'Hazard Detection Unit Implementation',
              'Testing Data Hazard Scenarios',
              'Pipeline Control Signals for Hazards',
              'Performance Evaluation'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Hazard Test Programs',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Expected Results Table',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 9,
            title: 'Control Hazards and Branch Prediction',
            duration: '150 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Exploring control hazards in the pipeline and techniques for branch prediction to minimize their performance impact.',
            topics: [
              'Control Hazard Basics',
              'Branch Penalty Analysis',
              'Static Branch Prediction',
              '1-Bit Dynamic Prediction',
              '2-Bit Saturating Counter Predictor',
              'Branch Target Buffer Design',
              'Industry Branch Predictors Overview'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Branch Prediction Slides',
                type: 'slides',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Predictor Performance Data',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 10,
            title: 'Branch Predictor Implementation',
            duration: '180 min',
            type: 'hands-on',
            description: 'Implement a 2-bit saturating counter branch predictor with a branch target buffer in your pipelined processor.',
            topics: [
              '2-Bit Predictor State Machine',
              'Branch History Table Design',
              'Branch Target Buffer Integration',
              'Mispredict Recovery Logic',
              'Pipeline Flush Mechanism'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Branch Predictor Verilog Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'BTB Implementation Example',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 11,
            title: 'Memory Hierarchy Integration',
            duration: '150 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Integrating instruction and data caches with the processor pipeline. Cache controller design and memory system considerations.',
            topics: [
              'Cache Basics Review',
              'Cache Controller Design',
              'Instruction Cache Integration',
              'Data Cache Design',
              'Memory Hierarchy Timing',
              'Cache Miss Handling in Pipeline'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Cache Integration Diagrams',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Cache Controller Verilog',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 12,
            title: 'Lab: Complete Processor Integration',
            duration: '210 min',
            type: 'lab',
            description: 'Final integration of all processor components and verification of the complete design using benchmark programs.',
            topics: [
              'Top Level Integration',
              'Interface Signal Verification',
              'Full System Testing',
              'Common Bug Resolution',
              'Performance Benchmarking',
              'Design Review Checklist'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'Benchmark Programs',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'System Integration Checklist',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 13,
            title: 'FPGA Implementation',
            duration: '240 min',
            type: 'lecture',
            description: 'Preparing the processor design for FPGA implementation, including synthesis considerations, timing constraints, and I/O interface design.',
            topics: [
              'FPGA Architecture Review',
              'Synthesis Optimization Techniques',
              'Timing Constraint Creation',
              'Clock Domain Design',
              'I/O Interface Implementation',
              'UART Communication for Testing'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'FPGA Implementation Guide',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Timing Constraints Template',
                type: 'code',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            id: 14,
            title: 'Final Project: RISC-V SoC',
            duration: '300 min',
            type: 'project',
            description: 'Design a complete RISC-V based System-on-Chip with peripheral interfaces. Implement and test the system on an FPGA platform.',
            topics: [
              'SoC Architecture Design',
              'Peripheral Bus Interface',
              'UART Implementation',
              'GPIO Controller Design',
              'Timer Module Implementation',
              'System Integration and Testing',
              'Performance Analysis'
            ],
            resources: [
              {
                name: 'SoC Architecture Template',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              },
              {
                name: 'Peripheral Interface Specifications',
                type: 'document',
                url: '#'
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        exercises: [
          {
            id: 1,
            title: 'ALU Implementation',
            description: 'Implement a complete ALU for the RISC-V RV32I instruction set supporting all arithmetic, logical, and shift operations.',
            difficulty: 'Moderate',
            estimatedTime: '2 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 2,
            title: 'Register File Design',
            description: 'Design a 32Ã—32-bit register file with dual read ports and a single write port. Implement the x0 register as a hardwired zero.',
            difficulty: 'Moderate',
            estimatedTime: '2 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 3,
            title: 'Control Unit Implementation',
            description: 'Design the control unit for the RISC-V processor that generates all necessary control signals based on instruction opcode and function fields.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '3 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 4,
            title: 'Single-Cycle Datapath Integration',
            description: 'Integrate all components into a functioning single-cycle RISC-V processor and test with basic instructions.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '4 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 5,
            title: 'Pipeline Register Design',
            description: 'Implement pipeline registers for a 5-stage RISC-V processor pipeline with appropriate control signal propagation.',
            difficulty: 'Moderate',
            estimatedTime: '2 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 6,
            title: 'Forwarding Unit Implementation',
            description: 'Design and implement the forwarding logic for resolving data hazards in the pipelined processor.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '3 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 7,
            title: 'Hazard Detection Unit',
            description: 'Implement the hazard detection unit that identifies pipeline hazards and generates stall signals for load-use data hazards.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '3 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 8,
            title: '2-Bit Branch Predictor',
            description: 'Implement a 2-bit saturating counter branch predictor with a simple branch target buffer.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '4 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 9,
            title: 'Pipeline Control for Exceptions',
            description: 'Extend the pipeline to handle basic exceptions and interrupts with appropriate pipeline flushing mechanisms.',
            difficulty: 'Advanced',
            estimatedTime: '5 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 10,
            title: 'Memory System Integration',
            description: 'Integrate a simple instruction cache and data cache with the processor pipeline, handling stalls on cache misses.',
            difficulty: 'Advanced',
            estimatedTime: '5 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 11,
            title: 'UART Controller',
            description: 'Implement a UART controller as a peripheral for your RISC-V processor to enable communication with a host computer.',
            difficulty: 'Challenging',
            estimatedTime: '4 hours'
          },
          {
            id: 12,
            title: 'Complete SoC Integration',
            description: 'Integrate your RISC-V processor with peripheral controllers into a complete System-on-Chip design.',
            difficulty: 'Advanced',
            estimatedTime: '6 hours'
          }
        ],
        resources: [
          {
            title: 'The RISC-V Instruction Set Manual',
            description: 'Official specification of the RISC-V instruction set architecture, covering the base and standard extension instruction sets.',
            type: 'Document',
            url: 'https://riscv.org/technical/specifications/'
          },
          {
            title: 'Digital Design and Computer Architecture: RISC-V Edition',
            description: 'Comprehensive textbook covering digital design principles and RISC-V architecture implementation.',
            type: 'Book',
            author: 'Sarah Harris and David Harris'
          },
          {
            title: 'Computer Organization and Design: The Hardware/Software Interface, RISC-V Edition',
            description: 'Classic computer architecture textbook updated for RISC-V, covering processor design principles.',
            type: 'Book',
            author: 'David Patterson and John Hennessy'
          },
          {
            title: 'RISC-V Assembler and Simulator',
            description: 'Online tool for writing and testing RISC-V assembly programs without hardware.',
            type: 'Tool',
            url: 'https://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/cs3410/2019sp/riscv/interpreter/'
          },
          {
            title: 'Verilog Quick Reference Guide',
            description: 'Concise reference for Verilog HDL syntax and constructs used in processor design.',
            type: 'Reference',
            url: '#'
          },
          {
            title: 'Pipelined Processor Design Slides',
            description: 'Detailed slides covering the principles and implementation of pipelined RISC-V processors.',
            type: 'Slides',
            url: '#'
          },
          {
            title: 'Branch Prediction Techniques: Survey and Taxonomy',
            description: 'Research paper surveying various branch prediction techniques and their performance characteristics.',
            type: 'Paper',
            author: 'Chen et al., IEEE Transactions on Computers'
          },
          {
            title: 'Industrial Processor Design Case Studies',
            description: 'Collection of case studies from commercial processor designs, highlighting real-world design decisions and trade-offs.',
            type: 'Document',
            url: '#'
          }
        ],
        faqs: [
          {
            question: 'What prior knowledge is required for this module?',
            answer: 'You should have a strong foundation in digital logic design, good understanding of Verilog HDL, and experience with combinational and sequential circuit design. Familiarity with computer architecture fundamentals is also recommended.'
          },
          {
            question: 'Will this module cover advanced RISC-V extensions like Vector instructions?',
            answer: 'This module focuses on the RV32I base integer instruction set. Advanced extensions are introduced conceptually but not implemented in the practical exercises. We offer a separate advanced module for Vector extension implementation.'
          },
          {
            question: 'What hardware/software tools are needed for this module?',
            answer: 'You will need a Verilog simulator (like ModelSim, VCS, or the open-source Icarus Verilog) for development and testing. For the FPGA implementation sections, you\'ll need Xilinx Vivado or Intel Quartus software and compatible FPGA hardware.'
          },
          {
            question: 'How does this module relate to professional processor design?',
            answer: 'This module teaches the core concepts and implementation techniques used in real-world processor design teams. While commercial processors are significantly more complex, the fundamentals you learn here are directly applicable to industry work, and many of our students have successfully transitioned to processor design roles at companies like ARM, Intel, and NVIDIA.'
          },
          {
            question: 'Can I use this processor design in my own projects?',
            answer: 'Yes, all the code you develop in this module is yours to use. The base code examples provided are available under an open-source MIT license, allowing you to build upon them for academic or commercial projects.'
          }
        ],
        quizzes: [
          {
            id: 1,
            title: 'RISC-V Architecture Fundamentals',
            questions: 8,
            estimatedTime: '20 min'
          },
          {
            id: 2,
            title: 'Pipeline Hazards and Resolution',
            questions: 12,
            estimatedTime: '30 min'
          },
          {
            id: 3,
            title: 'Branch Prediction Techniques',
            questions: 10,
            estimatedTime: '25 min'
          },
          {
            id: 4,
            title: 'Memory Hierarchy Design',
            questions: 10,
            estimatedTime: '25 min'
          }
        ],
        industryApplications: [
          {
            title: 'Mobile Processor Design',
            description: 'RISC-V is gaining adoption in mobile and IoT devices where energy efficiency is critical. The pipeline optimization and branch prediction techniques taught in this module are directly applicable to designing energy-efficient mobile processors.',
            companies: ['SiFive', 'Esperanto Technologies', 'Western Digital']
          },
          {
            title: 'Embedded Systems',
            description: 'The 32-bit RISC-V core you\'ll design in this module is suitable for a wide range of embedded applications from industrial control to consumer electronics, where customizability and IP ownership are important.',
            companies: ['Microchip', 'Andes Technology', 'GreenWaves Technologies']
          },
          {
            title: 'Academic Research',
            description: 'RISC-V has become the architecture of choice for computer architecture research due to its open nature. The skills from this module provide a foundation for research in specialized accelerators, security features, and novel microarchitectures.',
            institutions: ['UC Berkeley', 'ETH Zurich', 'IIT Madras']
          },
          {
            title: 'FPGA-based Acceleration',
            description: 'Custom RISC-V cores are increasingly used as control processors in FPGA-based accelerator designs for AI, networking, and storage applications, allowing tailored instruction sets for specific workloads.',
            applications: ['AI accelerators', 'Network packet processing', 'Storage controllers']
          }
        ],
        relatedModules: [
          {
            id: 8,
            title: 'System Verilog Basics',
            level: 'Intermediate',
            description: 'Learn SystemVerilog extensions for enhanced hardware design and verification capabilities.'
          },
          {
            id: 14,
            title: 'UVM Verification',
            level: 'Expert',
            description: 'Master Universal Verification Methodology (UVM) for advanced SystemVerilog testbenches.'
          },
          {
            id: 17,
            title: 'SoC Architecture',
            level: 'Advanced',
            description: 'Learn system-on-chip design principles including processor integration, memory hierarchies, and interconnects.'
          }
        ]
      };
      
      setModule(moduleData);
      setLoading(false);
    }, 800);
  }, [id]);

  const handleTabChange = (event, newValue) => {
    setTabValue(newValue);
  };

  if (loading) {
    return (
      <Box className="container page-container" sx={{ textAlign: 'center', py: 8 }}>
        <Typography variant="h5" sx={{ mb: 4 }}>Loading module content...</Typography>
        <LinearProgress color="primary" sx={{ mx: 'auto', width: '50%' }} />
      </Box>
    );
  }

  if (!module) {
    return (
      <Box className="container page-container" sx={{ textAlign: 'center', py: 8 }}>
        <Typography variant="h5">Module not found</Typography>
        <Button component={Link} to="/modules" sx={{ mt: 2 }}>
          Back to Modules
        </Button>
      </Box>
    );
  }

  return (
    <Box className="container page-container">
      {/* Breadcrumb */}
      <Breadcrumbs sx={{ mb: 2 }}>
        <Link to="/" style={{ textDecoration: 'none', color: 'inherit' }}>
          Home
        </Link>
        <Link to="/modules" style={{ textDecoration: 'none', color: 'inherit' }}>
          Modules
        </Link>
        <Typography color="text.primary">{module.title}</Typography>
      </Breadcrumbs>

      <Button 
        component={Link} 
        to="/modules" 
        startIcon={<ArrowBack />} 
        sx={{ mb: 3 }}
      >
        Back to Modules
      </Button>

      {/* Module Header */}
      <Box sx={{ position: 'relative', mb: 5 }}>
        <Box
          sx={{ 
            position: 'relative',
            height: '350px',
            borderRadius: 4,
            overflow: 'hidden',
            boxShadow: '0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)'
          }}
        >
          <Box
            component="img"
            src={module.image}
            alt={module.title}
            sx={{ 
              width: '100%', 
              height: '100%', 
              objectFit: 'cover',
            }}
          />
          <Box 
            sx={{ 
              position: 'absolute', 
              top: 0,
              left: 0,
              right: 0,
              bottom: 0, 
              background: 'linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.2), rgba(0,0,0,0.8))',
              display: 'flex',
              flexDirection: 'column',
              justifyContent: 'flex-end',
              p: { xs: 3, md: 5 }
            }}
          >
            <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', gap: 1, mb: 2 }}>
              <Chip 
                label={module.level} 
                size="small" 
                sx={{ 
                  backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15)', 
                  color: 'white',
                  fontWeight: 'bold',
                  backdropFilter: 'blur(10px)'
                }} 
              />
              <Chip 
                label={module.category} 
                size="small" 
                sx={{ 
                  backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15)', 
                  color: 'white',
                  fontWeight: 'bold',
                  backdropFilter: 'blur(10px)'
                }} 
              />
              <Chip 
                label={`${module.lessons.length} lessons`} 
                size="small" 
                sx={{ 
                  backgroundColor: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15)', 
                  color: 'white',
                  fontWeight: 'bold',
                  backdropFilter: 'blur(10px)'
                }} 
              />
            </Box>
            <Typography 
              variant="h2" 
              component="h1" 
              sx={{ 
                fontWeight: 'bold',
                color: 'white',
                textShadow: '0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)',
                mb: 2,
                fontSize: { xs: '2rem', sm: '2.5rem', md: '3rem' }
              }}
            >
              {module.title}
            </Typography>
            <Typography 
              variant="h6" 
              sx={{ 
                color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)',
                textShadow: '0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)',
                maxWidth: '800px',
                fontWeight: 'normal',
                lineHeight: 1.5
              }}
            >
              {module.description}
            </Typography>
            <Box sx={{ 
              display: 'flex', 
              alignItems: 'center', 
              mt: 3,
              color: 'white',
              gap: 3
            }}>
              <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                <Avatar 
                  src={module.instructor.avatar} 
                  alt={module.instructor.name}
                  sx={{ width: 40, height: 40, mr: 1 }}
                />
                <Box>
                  <Typography variant="body2" sx={{ opacity: 0.8 }}>Instructor</Typography>
                  <Typography variant="body1" sx={{ fontWeight: 'medium' }}>{module.instructor.name}</Typography>
                </Box>
              </Box>
              <Divider orientation="vertical" flexItem sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.3)' }} />
              <Box>
                <Typography variant="body2" sx={{ opacity: 0.8 }}>Last Updated</Typography>
                <Typography variant="body1" sx={{ fontWeight: 'medium' }}>{new Date(module.updatedAt).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', year: 'numeric' })}</Typography>
              </Box>
              <Divider orientation="vertical" flexItem sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.3)' }} />
              <Box>
                <Typography variant="body2" sx={{ opacity: 0.8 }}>Rating</Typography>
                <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                  <Typography variant="body1" sx={{ fontWeight: 'medium', mr: 0.5 }}>{module.rating}</Typography>
                  <Rating value={module.rating} precision={0.1} readOnly size="small" sx={{ color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)' }} />
                  <Typography variant="body2" sx={{ ml: 0.5, opacity: 0.8 }}>({module.studentsCount.toLocaleString()})</Typography>
                </Box>
              </Box>
            </Box>
          </Box>
        </Box>
      </Box>

      {/* Module Stats */}
      <Grid container spacing={2} sx={{ mb: 4 }}>
        <Grid item xs={6} sm={3}>
          <Paper sx={{ p: 2, height: '100%', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
            <People sx={{ color: 'primary.main', mr: 1 }} />
            <Box>
              <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">Students</Typography>
              <Typography variant="h6">{module.studentsCount.toLocaleString()}</Typography>
            </Box>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={6} sm={3}>
          <Paper sx={{ p: 2, height: '100%', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
            <Schedule sx={{ color: 'primary.main', mr: 1 }} />
            <Box>
              <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">Duration</Typography>
              <Typography variant="h6">{module.duration}</Typography>
            </Box>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={6} sm={3}>
          <Paper sx={{ p: 2, height: '100%', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
            <AutoStories sx={{ color: 'primary.main', mr: 1 }} />
            <Box>
              <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">Lessons</Typography>
              <Typography variant="h6">{module.lessons.length}</Typography>
            </Box>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={6} sm={3}>
          <Paper sx={{ p: 2, height: '100%', display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
            <Assignment sx={{ color: 'primary.main', mr: 1 }} />
            <Box>
              <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">Exercises</Typography>
              <Typography variant="h6">{module.exercises.length}</Typography>
            </Box>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
      </Grid>

      {/* Progress and Start buttons */}
      <Grid container spacing={2} sx={{ mb: 4 }}>
        <Grid item xs={12} md={8}>
          <Paper sx={{ p: 2 }}>
            <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" gutterBottom>
              Your Progress
            </Typography>
            <LinearProgress 
              variant="determinate" 
              value={module.completion} 
              sx={{ height: 10, borderRadius: 5, mb: 1 }} 
            />
            <Typography variant="body2">
              {module.completion}% Complete
            </Typography>
          </Paper>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item xs={12} md={4}>
          <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', gap: 2, height: '100%' }}>
            <Button 
              variant="contained" 
              color="primary" 
              fullWidth 
              startIcon={<PlayArrow />}
              component={Link}
              to={`/modules/${id}/lessons/1`}
              sx={{ height: '100%' }}
            >
              {module.completion > 0 ? 'Continue Learning' : 'Start Module'}
            </Button>
            <Button 
              variant="outlined" 
              color="primary"
              startIcon={<BookmarkAdd />}
              sx={{ flexShrink: 0 }}
            >
              Save
            </Button>
          </Box>
        </Grid>
      </Grid>

      {/* Tabs and Content */}
      <Box sx={{ mb: 4 }}>
        <Tabs 
          value={tabValue} 
          onChange={handleTabChange} 
          sx={{ 
            borderBottom: 1, 
            borderColor: 'divider',
            mb: 3,
            '& .MuiTab-root': {
              textTransform: 'none',
              fontSize: '1rem',
              fontWeight: 500
            }
          }}
        >
          <Tab label="Overview" icon={<MenuBook />} iconPosition="start" />
          <Tab label="Content" icon={<PlayCircleOutline />} iconPosition="start" />
          <Tab label="Exercises" icon={<Assignment />} iconPosition="start" />
          <Tab label="Instructor" icon={<People />} iconPosition="start" />
        </Tabs>

        {/* Overview Tab */}
        {tabValue === 0 && (
          <Box>
            <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>About This Module</Typography>
            <Typography paragraph sx={{ fontSize: '1.05rem', lineHeight: 1.6 }}>{module.overview}</Typography>
            
            {/* Learning Outcomes */}
            {module.learningOutcomes && (
              <>
                <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>What You'll Learn</Typography>
                <Paper elevation={0} variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 3, borderRadius: 2, mb: 4 }}>
                  <Grid container spacing={2}>
                    {module.learningOutcomes.map((outcome, index) => (
                      <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} key={index}>
                        <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'flex-start', mb: 1 }}>
                          <Check sx={{ color: 'success.main', mr: 1, mt: 0.3 }} />
                          <Typography variant="body1">{outcome}</Typography>
                        </Box>
                      </Grid>
                    ))}
                  </Grid>
                </Paper>
              </>
            )}
            
            {/* Prerequisites */}
            <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Prerequisites</Typography>
            <Paper elevation={0} variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 3, borderRadius: 2, mb: 4 }}>
              <List sx={{ display: 'grid', gridTemplateColumns: { xs: '1fr', sm: '1fr 1fr' }, gap: 1 }}>
                {module.prerequisites.map((prereq, index) => (
                  <ListItem key={index} sx={{ px: 1 }}>
                    <ListItemIcon sx={{ minWidth: 36 }}>
                      <Check sx={{ color: 'primary.main' }} />
                    </ListItemIcon>
                    <ListItemText primary={prereq} />
                  </ListItem>
                ))}
              </List>
            </Paper>

            {/* Skills */}
            <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Skills You'll Gain</Typography>
            <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: 1, mb: 4 }}>
              <Chip label="Verilog Syntax" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Module Design" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Behavioral Modeling" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Dataflow Modeling" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Structural Modeling" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Testbench Development" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Sequential Logic" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
              <Chip label="Combinational Logic" sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)', fontWeight: 500 }} />
            </Box>
            
            {/* Code Examples */}
            {module.codeExamples && (
              <>
                <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Code Examples</Typography>
                <Grid container spacing={3} sx={{ mb: 4 }}>
                  {module.codeExamples.map((example, index) => (
                    <Grid item xs={12} md={6} key={index}>
                      <Paper elevation={2} sx={{ p: 0, overflow: 'hidden', borderRadius: 2 }}>
                        <Box sx={{ p: 2, bgcolor: '#f5f5f5', borderBottom: '1px solid #e0e0e0' }}>
                          <Typography variant="subtitle1" fontWeight="medium">{example.title}</Typography>
                        </Box>
                        <Box sx={{ 
                          p: 2, 
                          bgcolor: '#272822',
                          color: '#f8f8f2',
                          fontFamily: 'monospace',
                          fontSize: '0.875rem',
                          overflow: 'auto',
                          maxHeight: '300px',
                          whiteSpace: 'pre'
                        }}>
                          {example.code}
                        </Box>
                      </Paper>
                    </Grid>
                  ))}
                </Grid>
              </>
            )}
            
            {/* Additional Resources */}
            {module.resources && (
              <>
                <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Additional Resources</Typography>
                <Paper elevation={0} variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 3, borderRadius: 2, mb: 4 }}>
                  <List>
                    {module.resources.map((resource, index) => (
                      <React.Fragment key={index}>
                        <ListItem sx={{ px: 1 }}>
                          <ListItemIcon>
                            {resource.type === 'PDF' ? 
                              <MenuBook color="primary" /> : 
                              <Assignment color="primary" />
                            }
                          </ListItemIcon>
                          <ListItemText 
                            primary={resource.title} 
                            secondary={resource.type} 
                          />
                          <Button variant="outlined" size="small" component="a" href={resource.url}>
                            Download
                          </Button>
                        </ListItem>
                        {index < module.resources.length - 1 && <Divider component="li" />}
                      </React.Fragment>
                    ))}
                  </List>
                </Paper>
              </>
            )}

            {/* Related Modules */}
            {module.relatedModules.length > 0 && (
              <>
                <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ mt: 4, borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Related Modules</Typography>
                <Grid container spacing={3}>
                  {module.relatedModules.map(relModule => (
                    <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4} key={relModule.id}>
                      <Card sx={{ height: '100%', display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', transition: 'transform 0.3s', '&:hover': { transform: 'translateY(-8px)' } }}>
                        <CardContent sx={{ flexGrow: 1 }}>
                          <Typography variant="h6" component="h3" gutterBottom>
                            {relModule.title}
                          </Typography>
                          <Chip 
                            label={relModule.level} 
                            size="small" 
                            sx={{ 
                              mb: 2,
                              backgroundColor: relModule.level === 'Beginner' ? '#e3f2fd' : 
                                            relModule.level === 'Intermediate' ? '#fff8e1' : '#fbe9e7',
                              color: relModule.level === 'Beginner' ? '#0277bd' : 
                                  relModule.level === 'Intermediate' ? '#ff8f00' : '#e64a19'
                            }} 
                          />
                          <Typography variant="body2" paragraph sx={{ mb: 2 }}>
                            {relModule.description}
                          </Typography>
                          <Button 
                            component={Link} 
                            to={`/modules/${relModule.id}`}
                            variant="outlined"
                            color="primary"
                            size="small"
                            fullWidth
                          >
                            View Module
                          </Button>
                        </CardContent>
                      </Card>
                    </Grid>
                  ))}
                </Grid>
              </>
            )}
          </Box>
        )}

        {/* Content Tab */}
        {tabValue === 1 && (
          <Box>
            <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Module Content</Typography>
            <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', mb: 3, gap: 2 }}>
              <Typography variant="body1">
                This module contains <strong>{module.lessons.length} lessons</strong> with a total duration of <strong>{module.duration}</strong>.
              </Typography>
              <Button 
                variant="contained" 
                color="primary" 
                startIcon={<PlayArrow />}
                component={Link}
                to={`/modules/${id}/lessons/1`}
                size="small"
              >
                Start Learning
              </Button>
            </Box>
            
            <Paper elevation={0} variant="outlined" sx={{ borderRadius: 2, overflow: 'hidden' }}>
              {module.lessons.map((lesson, index) => (
                <Box 
                  key={lesson.id}
                  sx={{ 
                    borderBottom: index < module.lessons.length - 1 ? '1px solid #e0e0e0' : 'none',
                  }}
                >
                  <Box 
                    sx={{ 
                      p: 2,
                      display: 'flex',
                      alignItems: 'flex-start',
                      cursor: 'pointer',
                      transition: 'background-color 0.2s',
                      '&:hover': {
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02)'
                      },
                      bgcolor: lesson.completed ? 'rgba(76, 175, 80, 0.05)' : 'transparent'
                    }}
                  >
                    <Box sx={{ mr: 2, mt: 0.5 }}>
                      {lesson.completed ? (
                        <Box sx={{ 
                          width: 32, 
                          height: 32, 
                          borderRadius: '50%', 
                          bgcolor: 'success.main',
                          color: 'white',
                          display: 'flex',
                          alignItems: 'center',
                          justifyContent: 'center'
                        }}>
                          <Check fontSize="small" />
                        </Box>
                      ) : (
                        <Box sx={{ 
                          width: 32, 
                          height: 32, 
                          borderRadius: '50%', 
                          border: '2px solid #e0e0e0',
                          color: 'text.secondary',
                          display: 'flex',
                          alignItems: 'center',
                          justifyContent: 'center',
                          fontWeight: 'bold'
                        }}>
                          {index + 1}
                        </Box>
                      )}
                    </Box>
                    
                    <Box sx={{ flexGrow: 1 }}>
                      <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', mb: 1, flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
                        <Typography variant="h6" component="h3" sx={{ mr: 2 }}>
                          {lesson.title}
                        </Typography>
                        <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', gap: 1, flexWrap: 'wrap' }}>
                          <Chip 
                            icon={lesson.type === 'video' ? <PlayCircleOutline fontSize="small" /> : <Assignment fontSize="small" />}
                            label={lesson.type} 
                            size="small"
                            sx={{ 
                              textTransform: 'capitalize',
                              bgcolor: lesson.type === 'video' ? '#e3f2fd' : '#fff8e1',
                              color: lesson.type === 'video' ? '#0277bd' : '#ff8f00',
                            }} 
                          />
                          <Chip 
                            label={lesson.duration} 
                            size="small"
                            sx={{ bgcolor: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)' }} 
                          />
                        </Box>
                      </Box>
                      
                      <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" paragraph>
                        {lesson.description}
                      </Typography>
                      
                      {lesson.topics && (
                        <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', flexWrap: 'wrap', gap: 0.5 }}>
                          {lesson.topics.map((topic, topicIndex) => (
                            <Chip 
                              key={topicIndex}
                              label={topic} 
                              size="small"
                              sx={{ 
                                fontSize: '0.7rem',
                                height: 24,
                                bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.08)'
                              }} 
                            />
                          ))}
                        </Box>
                      )}
                    </Box>
                    
                    <Button 
                      component={Link} 
                      to={`/modules/${id}/lessons/${lesson.id}`}
                      variant="outlined"
                      color="primary"
                      size="small"
                      sx={{ ml: 2, alignSelf: 'center', flexShrink: 0 }}
                    >
                      {lesson.completed ? 'Revisit' : 'Start'}
                    </Button>
                  </Box>
                </Box>
              ))}
            </Paper>
          </Box>
        )}

        {/* Exercises Tab */}
        {tabValue === 2 && (
          <Box>
            <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ borderLeft: '4px solid #6a0dad', pl: 2 }}>Practical Exercises</Typography>
            <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center', mb: 3 }}>
              <Typography variant="body1">
                Master your skills with these <strong>{module.exercises.length} hands-on exercises</strong>. Complete them to reinforce your learning.
              </Typography>
              <Chip 
                label={`${module.exercises.filter(ex => ex.completed).length}/${module.exercises.length} Completed`}
                color={module.exercises.filter(ex => ex.completed).length === module.exercises.length ? "success" : "default"}
                variant="outlined"
              />
            </Box>
            
            <Grid container spacing={3}>
              {module.exercises.map((exercise, index) => (
                <Grid item xs={12} md={6} key={exercise.id}>
                  <Paper 
                    elevation={0} 
                    variant="outlined" 
                    sx={{ 
                      p: 0, 
                      borderRadius: 2, 
                      overflow: 'hidden',
                      transition: 'transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s',
                      '&:hover': {
                        transform: 'translateY(-5px)',
                        boxShadow: 3
                      },
                      height: '100%',
                      display: 'flex',
                      flexDirection: 'column'
                    }}
                  >
                    <Box sx={{ 
                      p: 2,
                      borderBottom: '1px solid #e0e0e0',
                      bgcolor: exercise.difficulty === 'Easy' ? '#e8f5e9' : 
                             exercise.difficulty === 'Medium' ? '#fff8e1' : '#ffebee',
                    }}>
                      <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                        <Typography variant="h6" component="h3">
                          {exercise.title}
                        </Typography>
                        {exercise.completed && <Check color="success" />}
                      </Box>
                      <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', gap: 1, mt: 1 }}>
                        <Chip 
                          label={exercise.difficulty} 
                          size="small"
                          sx={{ 
                            bgcolor: 'white',
                            color: exercise.difficulty === 'Easy' ? '#2e7d32' : 
                                  exercise.difficulty === 'Medium' ? '#ff8f00' : '#d32f2f',
                            fontWeight: 'bold'
                          }} 
                        />
                        <Chip 
                          label={exercise.type} 
                          size="small"
                          sx={{ 
                            bgcolor: 'white',
                            textTransform: 'capitalize'
                          }} 
                        />
                        <Chip 
                          label={`${exercise.points} pts`}
                          size="small"
                          sx={{ bgcolor: 'white' }}
                        />
                      </Box>
                    </Box>
                    
                    <Box sx={{ p: 2, flexGrow: 1, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column' }}>
                      <Typography variant="body2" paragraph>
                        {exercise.description}
                      </Typography>
                      
                      <Box sx={{ 
                        display: 'flex', 
                        justifyContent: 'space-between', 
                        mt: 'auto', 
                        borderTop: '1px solid #e0e0e0',
                        pt: 2
                      }}>
                        <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
                          <Schedule fontSize="small" sx={{ mr: 0.5 }} />
                          Est. time: {exercise.estimatedTime}
                        </Typography>
                        
                        <Button 
                          component={Link} 
                          to={`/modules/${id}/exercises/${exercise.id}`}
                          variant="contained"
                          color="primary"
                          size="small"
                        >
                          {exercise.completed ? 'Review' : 'Start Exercise'}
                        </Button>
                      </Box>
                    </Box>
                  </Paper>
                </Grid>
              ))}
            </Grid>
          </Box>
        )}

        {/* Instructor Tab */}
        {tabValue === 3 && (
          <Box>
            <Paper elevation={0} variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 0, borderRadius: 2, overflow: 'hidden' }}>
              <Box sx={{ 
                p: 3, 
                bgcolor: 'rgba(106, 13, 173, 0.05)', 
                borderBottom: '1px solid #e0e0e0',
                display: 'flex',
                flexDirection: { xs: 'column', md: 'row' },
                alignItems: { xs: 'center', md: 'flex-start' },
                gap: 4
              }}>
                <Box sx={{ 
                  display: 'flex', 
                  flexDirection: 'column', 
                  alignItems: 'center',
                  width: { xs: '100%', md: '220px' } 
                }}>
                  <Avatar 
                    src={module.instructor.avatar} 
                    alt={module.instructor.name}
                    sx={{ 
                      width: 160, 
                      height: 160, 
                      mb: 2,
                      border: '4px solid white',
                      boxShadow: '0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)'
                    }}
                  />
                  <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom sx={{ textAlign: 'center' }}>
                    {module.instructor.name}
                  </Typography>
                  <Box sx={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', mb: 2 }}>
                    <Rating value={module.rating} precision={0.1} readOnly sx={{ mr: 1 }} />
                    <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">
                      {module.rating}/5 ({module.studentsCount.toLocaleString()} students)
                    </Typography>
                  </Box>
                  <Button 
                    variant="outlined" 
                    color="primary"
                    fullWidth
                    sx={{ mb: 1 }}
                  >
                    View Profile
                  </Button>
                  <Button 
                    variant="text" 
                    color="primary"
                    fullWidth
                  >
                    All Courses
                  </Button>
                </Box>
                
                <Box sx={{ flexGrow: 1 }}>
                  <Typography variant="h5" gutterBottom>About the Instructor</Typography>
                  <Typography paragraph sx={{ fontSize: '1.05rem', lineHeight: 1.6, mb: 3 }}>
                    {module.instructor.bio}
                  </Typography>
                  
                  {module.instructor.credentials && (
                    <>
                      <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>Credentials</Typography>
                      <List disablePadding>
                        {module.instructor.credentials.map((credential, index) => (
                          <ListItem key={index} sx={{ px: 0, py: 0.5 }}>
                            <ListItemIcon sx={{ minWidth: 36 }}>
                              <Check sx={{ color: 'success.main' }} />
                            </ListItemIcon>
                            <ListItemText primary={credential} />
                          </ListItem>
                        ))}
                      </List>
                    </>
                  )}
                </Box>
              </Box>
              
              <Box sx={{ p: 3 }}>
                <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>Other Modules by This Instructor</Typography>
                <Grid container spacing={2}>
                  <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4}>
                    <Paper variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 2, borderRadius: 2 }}>
                      <Typography variant="subtitle1" gutterBottom>Advanced Verilog Techniques</Typography>
                      <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" paragraph>
                        Master advanced Verilog concepts for complex digital systems design.
                      </Typography>
                      <Button size="small" color="primary">View Module</Button>
                    </Paper>
                  </Grid>
                  <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4}>
                    <Paper variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 2, borderRadius: 2 }}>
                      <Typography variant="subtitle1" gutterBottom>SystemVerilog for Verification</Typography>
                      <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" paragraph>
                        Learn hardware verification using advanced SystemVerilog features.
                      </Typography>
                      <Button size="small" color="primary">View Module</Button>
                    </Paper>
                  </Grid>
                  <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4}>
                    <Paper variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 2, borderRadius: 2 }}>
                      <Typography variant="subtitle1" gutterBottom>FPGA Design with Verilog</Typography>
                      <Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary" paragraph>
                        Implement your Verilog designs on real FPGA hardware.
                      </Typography>
                      <Button size="small" color="primary">View Module</Button>
                    </Paper>
                  </Grid>
                </Grid>
              </Box>
            </Paper>
          </Box>
        )}
      </Box>
    </Box>
  );
};

export default ModuleDetail;
